snippet.textDisplay:
So if you're an apple 🍏 user, you're being bias as far as the storage goes. The fact that we still have expandable storage, 128GB based storage is nothing to complain about. Samsung and Apple appears to be moving in different direction as far as their marketing strategies go. Apple has finally decided to go lower on their starting point with the hope to capitalize on their services, while Samsung has tweaked their model in favor of Apple's business model. They use the most premium hardware, marry it to great software and charge a price that creates a status quo.

I'm banking that Samsung launches these dull colors first because they know the specs is enough to allure enough consumers, which is a gamble, but they can afford to do that. Their next move will be to come out with better colors later this year to attract late adapters.

After which, they will lower the price by about $99. This is what I think they will do.

snippet.textDisplay:
Open Letter to Samsung:
Where is the focus on audio?


I know you want to sell disposable highly profitable Galaxy Buds, but come on now.


Why not challenge and beat LG's Quad dac and amp that comes alive with power hungry headphones, while still keeping the latest Hidef Bluetooth codecs for audio, LDAC, APTXHD, and add MQA decoding.


Not to mention better stereo recording with a standard app that allows layered recording at 24 bits, with editing features.
I understand the focus on video and photos, 8K, 4K, slo-mo, live mode, night mode.


And I appreciate the 128GB base (sorry apple), and ability to add more by sd cards (sorry apple), which you will need if you do a lot of video and photos.


But come on now..


120hz OLED color accurate, 6000 mah battery, 2 usb ports, and a headphone jack and class leading speakers are available in a ROG 2 phone for $589. with no hole, curve or notch in the display (which is a defective display)
I was really hoping, you used Lenovo's reverse notch (hood-crown), to give us a flat screen with no interruptions to the content on the display, like your tv's's monitors, and l;laptops.


And better stereo speakers, and a pro level dac and amp and 3.5 mm headphone jack, along with a 2.5 mm balanced jack on the ultra, and 2 sd cards, for backup, or extended recording.


Do not get me wrong, I am impressed with the tech, build quality, camera features, 865 chip, 5G, color options.


But like I , myself and other have said, you and almost every phone company ditches the headphone jack, not for thinness, not for water resistance, but just like Apple, to gain new revenue strings, once you introduce your own branded, disposable, $10 to make, $100-$250 to buy ear buds, and easy to lose dongles that are often rebought, and were never needed before.


This shows complete disrespect, to loyal Samsung users, who agreed with you trolling of apple's removal of the headphone jack, and we thought you cared about all of us equally wired or unwired, and you have one of the best headphone/hearing calibration apps.


I was truly hoping you would surpass LG in headphone audio, wired and wireless, and stereo recording, and the rumored Sony Walkman branded phones.
But no.


So I will stand by my commitment, as others will never to buy a smartphone without a good quality headphone jack standard, whether that be LG, Apple, Samsung, Google, One Plus, or whoever.


If you want my money and many others, you have to give us a feature that you took away for short term profits, when there was no need from our customer view to take it away.


It spoils the S 20 launch and leaves a bitter taste in the mouth.


So I look forward to Sony, LG, or even apple if they decide to bring back the headphone jack, we all know bluetooth can be hacked to gain access to your data, and may not be good that close to your brain for long amounts of time, we all have experienced cutouts, unpairing, and latency in games, But I still love my bluetooth headphones, and will not give them up, and will not consider a smartphone without bluetooth, neither will I consider a smartphone without a headphone jack, even though wires can get tangled and in the way, BT sounds almost as good, and the phone can be in the other room, etc.


Thanks for not listening samsung, to this customer, and putting audio last as a feature😟👎
